## Unrecognised Property

AG Grid does not recognise a property on the object shown in the message. Usually this is on your grid options or a column definition. It is almost always a typo in the property name, a property that belongs on a different object, or a property from a different version of the grid.

### Fix the property

Check the property name against the reference for the object it was set on, and correct any typo or misplaced property. The message lists the closest matching names as suggestions.

- [Grid Options](./grid-options/) for grid-level options
- [Column Properties](./column-properties/) for column definitions

### Properties added by a wrapper

A shared component that spreads unrelated props onto your grid options or column definitions surfaces every extra property as this warning. Where you can, remove the unrelated properties at the source.

### Storing your own data

To attach your own data to the grid options or a column, do not add it as a top-level property. Use the [`context`](./context/) property, which is provided on both grid options and column definitions for exactly this.
